        "body":"<p>&quot;So, what, you're just collecting up other people's tweets? And that passes for journalism these days?&quot;</p> <p>YES.</p> <p>We jest: there's far more substantial <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/music/morrissey\">Morrissey coverage here</a> – but that's not going to stop us combing social media to see what people are saying about the release of his book. It's 2013 you know, and that's just what happens.</p> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/robcastell100/statuses/390761582491230208\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>The Morrissey Autobiography. Has the <a href=\"https://twitter.com/guardian\">@guardian</a> ever been so excited about anything?... <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23maybethewire&amp;src=hash\">#maybethewire</a></p>— Rob Castell (@robcastell100) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/robcastell100/statuses/390761582491230208\">October 17, 2013</a></blockquote> </figure> <p>Frankly, Rob, NO. This is MORE exciting than <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/media/wire\">The Wire</a>, <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2013/jan/16/vegans-stomach-unpalatable-truth-quinoa\">quinoa</a> and <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/world/the-nsa-files\">the NSA files</a> put together. We've been so excited we dispatched Michael Hann to get a copy in the middle of the night, so he could speed-read it and be the first to see what Morrissey has to say for himself. Here's how Michael got on.</p> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/MichaelAHann/statuses/390609071130570752\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>14 of us at the Big Green Bookshop in Wood Green fighting for their 192 copies of the Mozzer book. The tension is palpable.</p>— Michael Hann (@MichaelAHann) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/MichaelAHann/statuses/390609071130570752\">October 16, 2013</a></blockquote> </figure> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-ca